itemDescription: member of the Women's Royal Naval Service, worked at Bletchley Park.

wikipedia_page.main: Margaret Elizabeth Cooper (née Douglas; 25 January  1918 – 18 July 2016) was a member of the Women's Royal Naval Service during the Second World War who worked at the signal interception and deciphering centre at Bletchley Park, England.

response: * Margaret Cooper (nurse) (1922–2013), English nurse and nurse-tutor
* Margaret Cooper (WRNS officer) (1918–2016), worked at the signal interception and deciphering centre at Bletchley Park, England
